  <section class="pycp-intro pycp-section" aria-labelledby="YakChewsDefinitionTitle">
    <div class="pycp-shell pycp-intro__grid">
      <div class="pycp-section-head">
        <p class="pycp-kicker">What they are</p>
        <h2 id="YakChewsDefinitionTitle">What are Himalayan yak cheese chews?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pycp-rich">
        <p>
          Himalayan yak chews are dense, hard cheese dog chews inspired by traditional mountain
          cheese-making from Nepal and the Himalayan region. Instead of relying on rawhide,
          artificial fillers, or highly processed textures, yak cheese dog chews start with a
          simple dairy base that is cooked, pressed, shaped, dried, and aged until it becomes a
          firm chew built for supervised enrichment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Dog owners choose natural dog chews like these because they combine simplicity with
          purpose. A properly sized yak chew can help redirect boredom, support calmer chew
          routines, and give dogs a satisfying job without the same rawhide concerns many modern
          pet parents are trying to avoid.
        </p>
        <div class="pycp-inline-links" aria-label="Related yak chew guides">
          <a href="/pages/best-rawhide-alternative">Compare rawhide alternatives</a>
          <a href="/blogs/dog-behavior/how-long-do-yak-chews-last">Read the chew duration guide</a>
          <a href="/pages/how-long-will-this-last-for-my-dog">Estimate your dog's chew time</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pycp-origin pycp-section" aria-labelledby="YakChewOriginTitle">
    <div class="pycp-shell pycp-feature">
      <div class="pycp-feature__image">
        <img
          src="{{ drying_image }}"
          alt="Pressed Himalayan yak cheese bars arranged on drying racks for aging"
          width="1672"
          height="941"
          loading="lazy"
        >
      </div>
      <div class="pycp-feature__copy">
        <p class="pycp-kicker">Nepal and the Himalayas</p>
        <h2 id="YakChewOriginTitle">A mountain-region tradition adapted for modern dogs.</h2>
        <p>
          The story behind Himalayan dog chews begins with a practical food tradition: preserving
          dairy in a region where patience, altitude, and careful preparation matter. Prime Pet Food
          Food draws from that cultural inspiration with respect, positioning yak cheese chews as
          a modern dog enrichment product rooted in a much older idea: simple ingredients made
          durable through time.
        </p>
        <p>
          That origin matters because it changes how the product feels. These are not novelty
          treats or generic long-lasting dog chews. They are dense, slow-crafted chews connected
          to Nepalese yak cheese traditions, then selected and packaged for today's dog parents
          who want cleaner ingredients and clearer trust.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pycp-process pycp-section" id="yak-chew-process" aria-labelledby="YakChewProcessTitle">
    <div class="pycp-shell">
      <div class="pycp-section-head pycp-section-head--center">
        <p class="pycp-kicker">The manufacturing process</p>
        <h2 id="YakChewProcessTitle">The step-by-step yak chew manufacturing process.</h2>
        <p>
          Every stage affects the final chew: texture, hardness, longevity, and the calm-time
          enrichment dogs get from a properly sized Himalayan yak chew.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pycp-timeline">
        <article class="pycp-step">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Milk collection</h3>
            <p>Traditional yak cheese starts with dairy collected from mountain-region herds. The goal is a simple base that can be transformed through heat, pressure, drying, and time.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step pycp-step--image">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">02</span>
          <div class="pycp-step__image">
            <img src="{{ boiling_image }}" alt="Traditional boiling process for Himalayan yak cheese curd formation" width="1672" height="941" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Traditional boiling</h3>
            <p>The milk is gently heated. This stage begins the transformation from liquid dairy into the dense cheese structure that eventually becomes a long-lasting dog chew.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Natural curd formation</h3>
            <p>As the mixture separates, curds form naturally. The curds are the foundation of the chew's final density and help create the firm texture yak cheese chews are known for.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">04</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Pressing process</h3>
            <p>The curds are pressed to remove excess moisture and tighten the structure. Less moisture means a firmer chew and a more satisfying supervised chewing experience.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step pycp-step--image">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">05</span>
          <div class="pycp-step__image">
            <img src="{{ drying_image }}" alt="Yak cheese chew bars shaped and drying on wooden racks" width="1672" height="941" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Shaping and drying</h3>
            <p>The pressed cheese is shaped into chew bars, then placed in a clean drying environment. The drying stage is where the chew begins to develop its signature hard texture.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">06</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Long aging and hardening</h3>
            <p>Time is the premium ingredient. As the bars continue to dry and harden, they become dense enough to support longer chew sessions for many dogs.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">07</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Quality inspection</h3>
            <p>Finished chews are reviewed for size, texture, and overall quality. This protects the consistency dog parents expect from a premium Himalayan yak chew.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="pycp-step pycp-step--image">
          <span class="pycp-step__num">08</span>
          <div class="pycp-step__image">
            <img src="{{ finished_image }}" alt="Finished Himalayan yak cheese dog chews being inspected before packaging" width="1672" height="941" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Packaging and delivery</h3>
            <p>After inspection, chews are prepared for modern dog homes: cleanly packed, easy to store, and ready for supervised enrichment routines.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pycp-benefits pycp-section" aria-labelledby="YakChewBenefitsTitle">
    <div class="pycp-shell pycp-benefits__grid">
      <div class="pycp-section-head">
        <p class="pycp-kicker">Why the process matters</p>
        <h2 id="YakChewBenefitsTitle">Slow craft creates a better long-lasting chew.</h2>
        <p>
          The traditional yak chew process is not just a story. It explains why the finished chew
          behaves differently from softer treats and many rawhide alternatives.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pycp-benefit-list">
        <article>
          <h3>Natural hardness</h3>
          <p>Pressing, drying, and aging reduce moisture and create the firm texture that helps yak chews last longer.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Simple ingredient philosophy</h3>
          <p>A minimal dairy-based recipe supports a cleaner label for dog parents comparing natural dog chews.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Rawhide-free enrichment</h3>
          <p>Yak cheese chews offer a dense chewing experience without using rawhide sheets or artificial fillers.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Calmer chew routines</h3>
          <p>Longer supervised chewing can help dogs focus, reduce boredom, and settle into a more satisfying ritual.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pycp-dog-owners pycp-section" aria-labelledby="DogOwnersYakChewsTitle">
    <div class="pycp-shell pycp-feature pycp-feature--reverse">
